Thanks for the refreshing point of view.<br>
<br>
Whatever mage that's quoted saying that it isn't worth getting rezzes is a liar.<br>
<br>
The mage charm is only useful in BoT.  The summoned mez is limited in use even more so than the charm.  High risk vs. reward is the name of the game when charming.  My level 59 charmed mobs quadding 500 (normally double attack only) with 140dd procs and 96percent haste happens to be the pinnacle of it.  When soloing I'm confined to one fairly safe area, the other area is more of a threat to public than I really enjoy.  The exp is significantly above average, 100% dependent on the random spawn table of elementals and giants (about 1:7 it seems) in the right rooms, and inconsistent at best.  I'm better off getting in a mid-range guild exp group, especially since people on dial-up can play an additional character out of group.<br>
<br>
