In my sig, yes Tupac did say that. It is indeed a paraphrase from Shakespeare, but Pac said those exact words in my sig, numerous times.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://216.40.249.192/mysmilies/contrib/guus/tong.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As far as the progression of this discussion, well, everyone is entitled to their opinion. There are always things that other classes can do that you and I will envy. With the blurring of the lines between classes becoming more and more apparent, we need to hold on to what we got.<br>
<br>
Enchanters have charm. Enchanters have haste. These are 2 of our class defining abilities. Let us haste our pets and die in peace!<br>
<br>
Desaran - I highly doubt that a mistake during a quad session is more likely to kill you than a charm breaking. I'd say we are about even. The majority of the time you have most of your mobs snared. Without snare, we are forced to rely on root/mez and pray we channel. <br>
<br>
Besides, Wizards have always been able to quad somewhere, from the time they got snare and their first AE nuke.<br>
<br>
The only time Enchanter charm solo + haste became an issue was after PoP and high damage mobs. Noone ever cared before.<br>
